---
import MarketingLayout from '../layouts/MarketingLayout.astro';

const title = 'Privacy | LocalPDF';
const description = 'Privacy principles and practical data-handling boundaries for the LocalPDF website and app.';
const canonical = 'https://localpdf.online/privacy';
const image = 'https://localpdf.online/og/home.svg';
---

<MarketingLayout title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical} image={image}>
  <div class="page-shell">
    <section class="section intro">
      <span class="eyebrow">Privacy</span>
      <h1>How LocalPDF talks about privacy in practical terms</h1>
      <p class="section-intro">
        This page explains how LocalPDF approaches privacy, document handling, and website behavior without relying on absolute claims.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2 class="section-title">Privacy position</h2>
      <div class="card-grid">
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Document handling</h3>
          <p>LocalPDF is positioned as a local-first PDF product. Sensitive-document workflows begin as close to the user device as possible.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Website behavior</h3>
          <p>The marketing site is still a website. Hosting, assets, and optional measurement tools are described honestly when they are enabled.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Public claims</h3>
          <p>Privacy copy stays aligned with the actual implementation. If the stack changes, the public wording changes with it.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2 class="section-title">Use and avoid</h2>
      <div class="two-col">
        <div class="policy-box good">
          <strong>Use language like this</strong>
          <ul class="bullet-list">
            <li>LocalPDF is built around local PDF workflows</li>
            <li>Sensitive-document tasks do not have to begin with a blind upload pattern</li>
            <li>Privacy claims stay consistent with the actual site stack and any enabled analytics configuration</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="policy-box bad">
          <strong>Avoid language like this</strong>
          <ul class="bullet-list">
            <li>Absolute “we collect nothing” claims unless that is fully true</li>
            <li>“No analytics” if analytics or telemetry are present</li>
            <li>“No third-party requests” if fonts, scripts, or hosted services are still in use</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section final-band">
      <div>
        <span class="eyebrow">Trust flow</span>
        <h2 class="section-title">Privacy is clearer when it stays close to product behavior</h2>
        <p class="section-intro">
          Read Security for the broader trust explanation and FAQ for the user-facing questions that come up before opening the app.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="cta-row">
        <a class="btn-primary" href="/security">Read Security</a>
        <a class="btn-secondary" href="/faq">Read FAQ</a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</MarketingLayout>

<style>
  .intro h1 {
    font-size: clamp(3rem, 5vw, 5rem);
    margin-top: 18px;
    margin-bottom: 18px;
    max-width: 11ch;
  }

  .two-col {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 18px;
  }

  .policy-box {
    padding: 22px;
    border-radius: 24px;
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    background: var(--surface);
  }

  .policy-box strong {
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: 14px;
    font-size: 1rem;
  }

  .policy-box.good {
    background: rgba(217, 235, 225, 0.42);
  }

  .policy-box.bad {
    background: rgba(243, 201, 146, 0.32);
  }

  .final-band {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 20px;
  }

  @media (max-width: 800px) {
    .two-col {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
